  "text": "We also run the different alternatives starting from the solution in [CITATION_1] , which gives the following improved objectives values: 1) 0.1395 2) 0.0565 3) 0.0455 4) 0.0447 5) 0.0466 6) 0.0449 7) 0.1391 8) 0.0454. We see that two methods were unable to improve the solution of [CITATION_2] to be close to the objective value 0.0447, which gives an indication that this solution is badly located. Indeed its very smallB matrix, 'blocked' near the positivity constraint, almost cancels the effect of the dynamical part of the filter: the solution in [CITATION_3] can be approximated by a static filter (theD matrix) with almost no impact (0.003%) on the objective 2 . On this matter we also mention that an important element for the performance of ILMIs is to try to stay away from the borders of the BMI feasible set (using e.g. [CITATION_4] Sec. 4.3] ), otherwise the algorithm may stall early at partial optimal solutions.",
